Utes are useful for a wide range of applications. You might be renovating your home and need to haul lots of stuff from place to place, be it paint, scaffolding, boxes, tools — you name it, the ute can probably carry it! Or you might be planning a little detour off-road, a 4 wheel drive ute like the Toyota Hilux can give you the traction you need to get wherever you want to go in and around Melbourne.

The city of Melbourne has plenty to offer, and what better way to make sure you can reach it all, and with whatever you need to carry, than with a low-cost, air-conditioned ute that you can rent short or long term? Sometimes a regular car just doesn’t have enough space. You might be travelling in a large group or transporting lots of luggage or big, heavy items. Our range of minibuses and people carriers, combined with our cost saving daily rates or deals on weekends or for long term rentals are perfect for a spontaneous road trip or something planned far in advance.

What better way to get around than in an 8 seater van with your favourite group? Alternatively, you might be a courier who needs to rent a van for a day or a long-term rental for multiple deliveries. Caterers or others looking to transport food can benefit from a refrigerated van that makes sure your produce stays fresh for as long as you need it to.
The Booking Terms and Conditions for this rental are provided by East Coast Car Rentals.  For the latest version of the Terms and Conditions please

Payment is made on collection of the rental vehicle. Your payment will be processed in our local currency, Australian dollars. We do not accept any other forms of currency. We accept debit and credit cards as the only form of payment – we do not accept cash.

We accept Visa, MasterCard debit and credit cards, as well as American Express. The use of American Express will incur a 2.2% surcharge. Visa and Master Card debit and credit cards do not incur a surcharge. International credit cards may also attract an International Transaction Fee from your financial institution.

In the event you have purchased and prepaid your rental on our website, or made a purchase through a travel agent or third-party website, you will need to provide proof of payment on collection of your vehicle.

Please note, it is important that the individual cardholder who originally made the booking is present for verification purposes at the time of collection of the vehicle. The cardholder is considered the primary driver a the time of booking and will need to provide the debit or credit card originally used when making the purchase. Once the debit or credit card has been verified, it is possible to finalise the booking and purchase additional options using another valid debit or credit card in the cardholder’s name.

As part of your rental purchase and at the time of collection of your vehicle, we will require a Holding Deposit to process your rental. A pre-authorisation will be be made on your debit or credit card with the funds being held by your financial institution. This amount can range from $0.00 to $1000.00 depending on the level of cover you choose. Upon safe return of the vehicle, East Coast Car Rentals will cancel the pre-authorisation. Please not the release of these funds is the responsibility of your financial institution and times can vary.
When booking directly with East Coast Car Rentals and choosing the Pay Now option, you also accept the cancellation and refund terms of the booking and the following associated fees:
No cancellation or refund fees apply when booking directly with East Coast Car Rentals with the Pay Later option.

Our Premium Roadside Assistance package protects you in the event something unexpected happens. While our standard breakdown service covers you for mechanical failure, this option will protect you when you just need a helping hand to get you on your way. We cover you for:
a. Tyre changing – help to fit the spare tyre of your rental vehicle
b. Lockout service – roadside assistance will attend to open your rental vehicle
c. Emergency fuel – if you run out of fuel up to 15 litres will be delivered at no extra charge
d. Flat battery – in the event you have left your lights on and the battery is flat, roadside assistance will jump start your vehicle
We’re here to help you 24/7. Select Premium Roadside Assistance at the time of your booking or at the retail counter on collection of your vehicle.

All Rentals require a Security deposit/bond. Atlas does not accept CASH as a security deposit/bond for your rental Vehicle, only Credit Cards – MasterCard & Visa or Visa Debit Cards & MasterCard Debit Cards. The name on the credit card must match the name on the hirer’s drivers licence. (Prepaid credit cards are not accepted) The Security Deposit is charged to the card and is refunded up to 10 business after the return of the vehicle if all outstanding amounts have been settled (*Subject to the Terms and Conditions).

All drivers are responsible for any fines received. When ATLAS receives a fine, a statutory declaration is completed whereby you will be nominated as the driver of the vehicle and signed by the relevant authority. An administration fee will be charged for this service and the funds debited from your supplied credit card.
